mobileApp.text1:
The RocketSidekick mobile application (for Android, and eventually iOS) provides additional capabilities that 
provides some additional capabilities that are focused in the field usage.  Not all of the capabilities will be available on both
applications.

The mobile applications capabilities are:

* Ability to calculate Thrust to Weight ratios
* Ability to search motors via ThrurstCurve.org's applications
* Search results are cached on the mobile device
	* Create and maintain <sup>1</sup>
	* Launch preparation checklists
	* Rocket inventory
	* Parachute inventory
	* Altimeter inventory
	* GPS Tracker inventory
* Execute a preparation checklist for a launch
* Track launches and success or failure of the launch <sup>1</sup>

<sup>1</sup> Items marked with an asterik will also sync with the web application and may also be available to maintain within the web application.

epoxy.desc: Chart comparing specifications of some common epoxies, plus some additional links about epoxies and model rocketry.

highPower.welcome1: High power rocketry is a subset of model rocketry that deals with higher power, thus the name, rocket motors.
highPower.welcome1NAR: Rocket motors which exceed model rocketry motor definitions and the models that use these motors are collectively referred to as High Power Rocketry (HPR). HPR is similar to model rocketry with differences that include the propulsion power and weight increase of the model. They use motors in ranges over “G” power and/or weigh more than laws and regulations allow for unrestricted model rockets.
highPower.welcome2: This section provides a collection of links to various content, information and tools about high power rocketry!

simulators.desc: A nice article about simulators for model rocketry by ThrustCurve.org.

flightInfo.desc: Utility to create a graphical flight chart with flight information from altimeters for use in posting to websites, in videos, etc. Currently only Eggtimer output is supported.

flightPath.desc: Utility to create a KML file based on GPS tracker output that can be imported into Google Earth.  Currently only the Featherweight GPS tracker is supported.

foam.title: Foam Volume for Fin Cans
foam.desc: Calculations of required volume of expanding foam for a given fin can dimensions.

thrust2Weight.title: Thrust to Weight
thrust2Weight.desc: Utility to determine thrust to weight ratios for rockets and different motors, either manually entered or from ThrustCurve.org.
thrust2Weight.mass_hint: Weight of the rocket fully loaded including engines.
thrust2Weight.guidance: Initial thrust is more important during the initial boost phase off the launch pad.  Average thrust is the average of the thrust across the burn timespan.  The peak thrust does not always occur during launch or initial boost phase; consult the thrust curves at
thrust2Weight.guidance2: When using a ThrustCuve motor profile, the initial thrust is a approximate value and is determined from the sample data included with the motor profile.  The largest thrust (N) sample that falls below the Max. Launch Rod Time specified is used.

content.welcome: RocketSidekick hosts a variety of tools in once place for model rocketry.  Some of the tools are custom build, others are based on formulas found in variety of rocketry forums and sites, as well as some sections having links or information.
content.welcome1a: Contributions for additional tools are welcome via Pull Requests on the site's GitHub repo (
content.welcome1b: ).  See the documentation on the repo.
content.welcome2: The following is the selection of tools and information currently available.
content.welcome3: A high level primer on what the exciting world of model rocketry is!
